      <h1>MISSION</h1>
      <section class="mission-section">
        <h2>SPIRITUALITY</h2>
        <ph>
          To be witness of our faith by cultivating a spirituality rooted on the Word of God, nourished by the sacraments, and lived in humble loving service especially to the poor.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section class="mission-section">
        <h2>TRANSFORMATIVE EDUCATION</h2>
        <p>
          To provide Catholic education leading to a conversion that transforms persons and communities.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section class="mission-section">
        <h2>ADVOCACY</h2>
        <p>
          To uphold the principles of social justice, peace, truth and ecological stewardship towards an engaged citizenship.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section class="mission-section">
        <h2>RESEARCH</h2>
        <p>
          To foster a vibrant and stimulating culture of research.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section class="mission-section">
        <h2>SYNODALITY</h2>
        <p>
          To promote a culture of care, dialogue, and collaboration among all the stakeholders as a dynamic participation in the life and mission of the church.
        </p>
      </section>
